<dl id="n08053o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08053o">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08053o"> 53(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> doubtful points <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08053o"><li>FW 114.09 </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n08053o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n08053o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08053o">MS BL 47473-23</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:315 <a name="e4d2" href="../../FF/fdra/eda.htm#e4d2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/ed2.htm#n08053o">Draft: I.5&sect;4.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Voici (fig. 96) l&apos;&eacute;criture h&eacute;sitante et lente d&apos;un d&eacute;bile peu cultiv&eacute;. Il est &acirc;g&eacute; de trente ans. En suivant le trac&eacute; lettre par lettre on se rend compte de l&apos;influence &eacute;norme de son ignorance sur la rapidit&eacute; de son &eacute;criture. Ne sachant pas l&apos;orthographe, il s&apos;arr&ecirc;te &agrave; presque chaque mot en reposant, dans l&apos;intervalle, la plume sur le papier, d&apos;o&ugrave; les points o&ugrave; il n&apos;en faut pas. Sa main manque d&apos;assurance et tremble. <br><font color="green">[This (fig. 96) is the hesitant and slow writing of an idiot with very little education. He is thirty. In following the stroke letter by letter, we realise the enormous influence of his ignorance on the speed of his writing. Since he does not know how to spell, he stops at almost every word while resting the pen, in the meantime, on the paper, which explains the periods where there should not be any. His hand lacks assurance and trembles.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 194</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
